00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:57.970
for chaos, for ambiguity.

00:03:57.970 --> 00:04:00.950
They had this desire to
make meaning out of chaos.

00:04:00.950 --> 00:04:02.140
They were non-conformist.

00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:05.170
They were unconventional,
risk-takers.

00:04:05.170 --> 00:04:08.810
They were kind of originals
and very individual.

00:04:08.810 --> 00:04:11.150
So he found that
this very messy mix

00:04:11.150 --> 00:04:13.090
of things, which is
where we kind of got

00:04:13.090 --> 00:04:15.215
this idea of-- well,
one of the places we

00:04:15.215 --> 00:04:17.839
got this idea of the messy minds
of the highly creative person,

00:04:17.839 --> 00:04:20.000
that they can't be boiled
down to one single thing.

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:23.190
It's this complex sort of
host of characteristics

00:04:23.190 --> 00:04:24.522
that seem to inform creativity.

00:04:24.522 --> 00:04:25.730
SCOTT BARRY KAUFMAN: Totally.

00:04:25.730 --> 00:04:31.230
We want to rebrand having a
messy mind as a good thing.

00:04:31.230 --> 00:04:34.479
In schools, we promote
efficiency, right?

00:04:34.479 --> 00:04:36.520
We say, OK, well you have
to do well on this test

00:04:36.520 --> 00:04:37.744
and you can't revise it.

00:04:37.744 --> 00:04:39.660
You have to do well on
this standardized test.

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:42.450
But when we study
these creative geniuses

00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:45.370
or these great creators, you
see they're not characterized

00:04:45.370 --> 00:04:46.719
by their efficiency.

00:04:46.719 --> 00:04:48.510
They're characterized
by their variability.

00:04:48.510 --> 00:04:50.510
They're characterized by
their trial and error,

00:04:50.510 --> 00:04:55.080
their risk-taking, their
openness to experiences,

00:04:55.080 --> 00:04:56.250
their sensitivity.

00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:59.860
And a lot of times,
their sensitivity

00:04:59.860 --> 00:05:02.360
can seemingly get in the way
of their creative process.

00:05:02.360 --> 00:05:04.950
But you find that it
is through reconciling

00:05:04.950 --> 00:05:07.410
all of these contradictions
within themselves that you

00:05:07.410 --> 00:05:10.182
find creativity is
most likely to emerge.

00:05:10.182 --> 00:05:11.640
We also found lots
of contradiction

00:05:11.640 --> 00:05:13.275
with introversion
and extroversion.

